    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>Julius Caesar, revered by the people, assassinated by the senate. Rumors murmur of his return. Whispers speak of white piercing eyes and the chaotic grin of a man-turned deity. Time has passed since the Ides of March but not time enough to sheath the daggers of betrayal. Fear drove the actions of his conspirators, now it is fear that has driven them to flee. One by one these wounds will be closed.</i> </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3196870/extras/2f33ad948c34d2c4c36fb22af3be7183.poster.avif?t=1769159916\" width=616 height=336 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3196870/extras/2f33ad948c34d2c4c36fb22af3be7183.webm?t=1769159916\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3196870/extras/2f33ad948c34d2c4c36fb22af3be7183.mp4?t=1769159916\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Original soundtrack for Caesar's Revenge. 50 minutes of thrash metal composed for the game by its developers.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Produced in Reaper, recorded using an ESP LTD EC401.</p>",
